Benakat, Buana Listya, Semen Gresik: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-09-05T02:05:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/benakat-buana-listya-semen-gresik-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.1 percent to 3,841.73 on
Aug. 26. The market was closed Aug. 29 to Sept. 2 for public
holidays.  Energy companies: Crude oil for October delivery fell 2.8
percent to $86.45 a barrel in  New York  on Sept. 2, the biggest
drop since Aug. 18. The contract slid 0.7 percent to $85.83 a
barrel in after-hours trading.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 2.1 percent to 2,375 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, was
unchanged at 191 rupiah.  PT Bakrie & Brothers (BNBR IJ): The  investment company 
plans to build an explosives plant in Kalimantan next year at a
cost of $300 million, Kontan reported, citing Finance Director
Eddy Soeparno. Bakrie & Brothers was unchanged at 64 rupiah.  PT Benakat Petroleum Energy (BIPI IJ): The Indonesian  oil
company  plans to buy a 10 percent stake in PT Buana Listya Tama
(BULL IJ) this year at a cost of about 300 billion rupiah ($35
million), Investor Daily Indonesia reported. Benakat declined 2
percent to 98 rupiah and Buana Listya, which provides freight
transportation services, was unchanged at 146 rupiah.  PT Semen Gresik (SMGR IJ): Indonesia’s biggest cement
producer expects to increase output to 23 million tons next year
from 20.2 million tons this year, Investor Daily Indonesia
reported, citing President Director Dwi Soetjipto. Semen Gresik
was unchanged at 9,100 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  